full_text:
Interesting as well because the civil aircraft band uses AM modulation
on VHF frequencies. AM is a messy bugger, seems to bleed over
everywhere. Civil aircraft also use SSB (Sideband) on HF, but usually
only on intercontinental flights.

thanks
Andy






