&gt; Well I was simplifying but most broadcast antennas are setup for
very little radiation directly below as well as above as it is a waste
of power.  AM *loves* to shoot straight up because of the bounce (as
you HAM guys know) but TV and FM wants as much power as possible to be
at the top for the farthest line of sight broadcast.
&gt; 
&gt; I was amazed to read that you guys got FM chatter on the recorder. 
I guess it is possible in theory but I would never had expected that.
 Just goes to show why it is all radio theory and not radio proof or
law :))  Those EM fields are tricky little buggers.
&gt; 
&gt; Don
&gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; --- On Mon, 12/15/08, Zack Widup &lt;w9sz@...&gt; wrote:
